title: 3Sum
description: Given an integer array nums, return all the triplets [nums[i], nums[j], nums[k]] such that i != j, i != k, and j != k, and nums[i] + nums[j] + nums[k] == 0. Notice that the solution set must not contain duplicate triplets.
input_format: A single line containing the array `nums` separated by spaces.
output_format: Print each triplet on a new line, with elements separated by spaces. The triplets and elements within triplets can be in any order (the judge checks for set equality).
